clicker question here.

29
00:01:14,645 --> 00:01:17,920

30
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:20,630
So the question is which
treatment would you

31
00:01:20,630 --> 00:01:22,110
choose if you
needed a treatment?

32
00:01:22,110 --> 00:01:25,870
Treatment 1 cured
100% of the patients.

33
00:01:25,870 --> 00:01:29,060
Treatment 2 cured
95% in a trial.

34
00:01:29,060 --> 00:01:31,930
And treatment 3 cured 90%.

35
00:01:31,930 --> 00:01:34,835
So with this information
which would you choose?

36
00:01:34,835 --> 00:01:39,229

37
00:01:39,229 --> 00:01:40,770
AUDIENCE: With only
this information?

38
00:01:40,770 --> 00:01:41,853
PROFESSOR: With only this.

39
00:01:41,853 --> 00:01:44,610
If this is all I told you.

40
00:01:44,610 --> 00:01:46,020
Which would you choose?

41
00:01:46,020 --> 00:01:48,785
I recognizing that you might
not be too happy with just

42
00:01:48,785 --> 00:01:52,430
this information, but if this
is their best information, what

43
00:01:52,430 --> 00:01:53,590
would you choose?

44
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:57,110
All right, there's some
hold outs for the 95% cure.

45
00:01:57,110 --> 00:02:00,470
I'm not sure why.

46
00:02:00,470 --> 00:02:02,740
Really, that 95%
was just, you know,

47
00:02:02,740 --> 00:02:08,139
they've cured one
person 19 out of 20.

48
00:02:08,139 --> 00:02:11,640
They got them 19 out of 20
well, or however you say that.

49
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:12,390
Yeah.

50
00:02:12,390 --> 00:02:16,880
All right, so there's
even a few more holdouts.

51
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:20,790
All right, what if I gave
you this information?

52
00:02:20,790 --> 00:02:24,590
Treatment 1 cured 3
out of 3 patients.

53
00:02:24,590 --> 00:02:26,430
That's 100%.

54
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:28,990
Treatment 2 cured
19 of 20 patients.

55
00:02:28,990 --> 00:02:32,226
That's 95%.

56
00:02:32,226 --> 00:02:33,600
Or, you have a
standard treatment

57
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:38,920
which has cured 90,000 out
of 100,000 patients, 90%,

58
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:41,120
in clinical practice.

59
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,490
Now which one would you choose?

60
00:02:42,490 --> 00:02:49,832

61
00:02:49,832 --> 00:02:51,290
PROFESSOR 2: It's
very interesting.

62
00:02:51,290 --> 00:02:53,706

63
00:02:53,706 --> 00:02:54,747
Yeah, it totally changed.

64
00:02:54,747 --> 00:02:55,670
PROFESSOR: What's that?

65
00:02:55,670 --> 00:02:56,580
PROFESSOR 2: It totally shifted.

66
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:58,360
PROFESSOR: It totally
shifted, really?

67
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:00,734
PROFESSOR 2: We have a bunch
of very conservative people.

68
00:03:00,734 --> 00:03:02,400
PROFESSOR: Right.

69
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:06,800
So the majority would
choose the third choice,

70
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:09,720
90 out of 100,000.

71
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:13,554
I think-- well someone tell
me, what's the intuition there?

72
00:03:13,554 --> 00:03:15,330
AUDIENCE: Because
it's been more tested.

73
00:03:15,330 --> 00:03:16,705
PROFESSOR: It's
been more tested.

74
00:03:16,705 --> 00:03:20,480
